<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3864] Spatial maxDetailDist doesn&apos;t follow degrees standardization</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3864</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Technically this bug is in Lucene spatial but it&apos;s on a factory that is only really used by the Solr adapter, plus I added a mandatory attribute so I decided to file it here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The maxDetailDist attribute on SpatialRecursivePrefixTreeFieldType is interpreted as kilometers for a geospatial context.  However, for this first release of spatial, all distances are standardized on degrees.  Of course I want to support kilometers but not inconsistently and there isn&apos;t time for that right now.  Because this is likely to be a common problem of interpreting distances for this field, I decided to add a mandatory attribute &quot;units&quot; which must be &quot;degrees&quot;.  When kilometers is supported then it will be added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, the name &quot;maxDetailDist&quot; as a name isn&apos;t so great. As part of some renames related to this sort of thing a month back I overlooked this one.  I think &quot;maxDistErr&quot; is better and more consistent with attributes such as &quot;distErr&quot; you can put in shape query.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
